setTimeout runs & executes a function after a specified delay of milliseconds. How many times? 
Just once, but you can go around that if you have another setTimeout inside your function to call itself again 
Just like setInterval, but with a different time delay. So,
var time = 0;
setTimeout  == if(time>3000) { //function }
setInterval   == while(time==3000) { if(time>3000) {time=0;} //function }
